This paper is about a conversational agent that uses deep learning, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the agent needs to detect and respond to abusive language, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of building an agent that can meet a wider range of user social needs, which could fall under the categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper mentions that the agent has interacted with millions of users, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
